Privacy Policy
Last updated: April 27, 2025

Introduction
At PicIDify, we take your privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our ID photo processing application.

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information
When you use PicIDify, we may collect:

Photos you upload for processing
Device information (model, OS version)
Usage statistics and crash reports
IP address and network information
1.2 How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information to:

Process and enhance your ID photos
Improve our app's performance and features
Provide customer support
Ensure app security and prevent fraud
2. Data Storage and Security
We implement appropriate security measures to protect your information:

Encrypted data transmission
Secure cloud storage
Regular security audits
Limited employee access to personal data
3. Third-Party Services
We may use third-party services for:

Cloud storage and processing
Analytics and crash reporting
Payment processing
4. Your Rights
You have the right to:

Access your personal data
Request data deletion
Opt-out of data collection
Export your data
5. Data Retention
We retain your data for:

Processed photos: 30 days
Account information: Until account deletion
Usage statistics: 1 year
6. Children's Privacy
PicIDify is not intended for users under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

7. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy on this page.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: privacy@picidify.com
Address: [Your Company Address]
9. Legal Compliance
This Privacy Policy complies with:

General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
Other applicable data protection laws
